    38	- The academic runtime shadow-state layer persists tasks, drafts, cell values, locks, timetable templates, task placements, and calendar audit data through dedicated runtime keys and compatibility routes.
    39	- The student-shell and risk-explorer routes are indirect drilldown surfaces that remain available to academic roles and `SYSTEM_ADMIN`, but the message/session APIs still enforce active-run and student-scope checks.
    40	- The teaching portal homes resolve to `dashboard` for Course Leader, `mentees` for Mentor, and `department` for HoD; the shared drilldown pages are `student-history`, `student-shell`, `risk-explorer`, `queue-history`, and `faculty-profile`.
    41	- `src/system-admin-request-workspace.tsx` exposes only the status-driven `Take Review` / `Approve` / `Mark Implemented` / `Close` control path, while `air-mentor-api/src/modules/admin-requests.ts` still supports `Needs Info` and `Rejected` transitions.
    42	- The HoD `unlock-review` page is a separate academic unlock workflow, not the sysadmin admin-request queue.
